Silvestri
</taxonomicName>
, by original designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1436,1311,1552]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,310,1311,1336]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" reason="1">Introduction.</emphasis>
At present, 20 species of 
<taxonomicName box="[604,789,1313,1336]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Eumyrmococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[604,789,1313,1336]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Eumyrmococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are known (
<bibRefCitation author="Schneider, S. A. &amp; LaPolla, J. S." box="[926,1235,1311,1335]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="57 - 82" refId="ref60232" refString="Schneider, S. A. &amp; LaPolla, J. S. (2011) Systematics of the mealybug tribe Xenococcini (Hemiptera: Coccoidea: Pseudococcidae), with a discussion of trophobiotic associations with Acropyga Roger ants. Systematic Entomology, 36, 57 - 82." type="journal article" year="2011">Schneider &amp; LaPolla, 2011</bibRefCitation>
), divided into two species-groups, the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="De Lotto" baseAuthorityYear="1977" box="[375,537,1348,1372]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Eumyrmococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scorpioides">
<emphasis box="[375,537,1348,1372]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">E. scorpioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group with three species and the 
<taxonomicName box="[1013,1122,1348,1372]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Eumyrmococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smithii">
<emphasis box="[1013,1122,1348,1372]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">E. smithii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group with 17 species. Adult males are only known for the latter species-group: 
<taxonomicName authority="Williams" authorityName="Williams" box="[870,1164,1383,1408]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Eumyrmococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sarawakensis">
<emphasis box="[870,1054,1384,1408]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">E. sarawakensis</emphasis>
Williams
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1181,1263,1383,1407]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="52.[151,250,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[158,1403,178,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-66@52.[150,1436,143,1909]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURE 16. Eumyrmococcus sarawakensis Williams. Adult male. Where J = 2 dorsal views of posterior end of abdomen, L = 2 ventral views of posterior end of abdomen, and V = minute setae. For other labels, see under Materials and methods: conventions. (Modified after Williams, 1998)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5250082" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5250082/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Williams" authorityName="Williams" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Eumyrmococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taylori">
<emphasis box="[1329,1436,1384,1408]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">E. taylori</emphasis>
Williams
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[268,348,1419,1443]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="54.[151,250,1920,1943]" captionTargetBox="[183,1385,221,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-64@54.[151,1436,193,1899]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 18. Eumyrmococcus taylori Williams. Adult male. Where J = dorsal view of posterior end of abdomen; L = ventral view of penial sheath, and V = minute capitate setae. For other labels, see under Materials and methods: conventions. (Modified after Williams, 1998)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5250086" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5250086/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Williams, D. J." box="[371,547,1419,1443]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref60747" refString="Williams, D. J. (1998) Mealybugs of the genera Eumyrmococcus Silvestri and Xenococcus Silvestri associated with the ant genus Acropyga Roger and a review of the subfamily Rhizoecinae (Hemiptera, Coccoidea, Pseudococcidae). Bulletin of the Natural History Museum. Entomology Series (London), 67, 1 - 64." type="journal article" year="1998">Williams, 1998</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<taxonomicName authority="Silvestri (Kishimoto-Yamada et al., 2005)" box="[615,1198,1419,1444]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Eumyrmococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smithii">
<emphasis box="[615,722,1420,1444]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">E. smithii</emphasis>
Silvestri (
<bibRefCitation author="Kishimoto-Yamada, K. &amp; Itioka, T. &amp; Kawai, S." box="[836,1190,1419,1444]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="3501 - 3524" refId="ref59245" refString="Kishimoto-Yamada, K., Itioka, T. &amp; Kawai, S. (2005) Biological characterization of the obligate symbiosis between Acropyga sauteri Forel (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) and Eumyrmococcus smithii Silvestri (Hemiptera: Pseudococcidae: Rhizoecinae) on Okinawa Island, southern Japan. Journal of Natural History, 39 (40), 3501 - 3524" type="journal article" year="2005">
Kishimoto-Yamada 
<emphasis box="[1063,1112,1420,1444]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">et al</emphasis>
., 2005
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1213,1296,1419,1443]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="53.[151,247,1977,2000]" captionTargetBox="[246,1344,153,1969]" captionTargetId="figure-57@53.[239,1359,97,1997]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="FIGURE 17. Eumyrmococcus smithii Silvestri. Adult male. Where L = ventral view of penial sheath, and N = side view of posterior end of abdomen. For other labels, see under Materials and methods: conventions. (Modified after Kishimoto-Yamada et al., 2005)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5250084" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5250084/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). These can be separated using the key below. A generic diagnosis and key to the identification of the adult females of all 20 species can be found in Schnieder and LaPolla (2011).
</paragraph>
